developed cutting edge services but became isolated from global markets it offers rich areas for political economy research that can provide implications for developments elsewhere related jsp activities include speaker series workshops and publications contact kenji kushida publications cover diffusing the cloud cloud computing and implications for public policy kenji kushida jonathan murray john zysman journal of industry competition and trade 2011 html+ cover leading without followers how politics and market dynamics trapped innovations in japan's domestic galapagos telecommunications sector kenji kushida journal of industry competition and trade 2011 html+ cover the services transformation and network policy the new logic of value creation kenji kushida john zysman review of policy research vol 26 1 2 2009 html+ cover wireless bound and unbound the politics shaping cellular markets in japan and south korea kenji kushida journal of information technology and politics vol 5 2 2008 html+ cover the political economies of broadband development in korea and japan kenji kushida seung youn oh asian survey vol 47 3 2007 html+ events & presentations the future of mobile internet japan lessons from the 2011 disaster december 8 2011 seminar series tadashi onodera search aparc search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 9741 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
